# Trivy ignore file — accepted risks with justification
# Format: CVE-YYYY-XXXXX [expiry] [comment]

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem@2026.1.14 — transitive node_modules
#
# These CVEs are in packages bundled INSIDE the MCP filesystem server (a
# third-party tool we don't own). They cannot be patched by us — the MCP server
# locks its own dependency tree via package-lock.json. Mitigations in place:
#   • The MCP server process runs as non-root (appuser)
#   • Filesystem access is scoped to the current working directory only
#   • The server is not exposed to untrusted external input
# Action: re-evaluate when @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem releases a
#         version with updated transitive dependencies.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# cross-spawn < 7.0.5 — ReDoS in shell argument parsing
